<br>
I don't know how useful that would really be, since you're probably taking the melee out of the fight for at least 20 seconds or so, but I suppose if the melee gets any damage in after the heal it's better than if he had died.<br>
<br>
I had this available to me for a Vox raid I was leading and decided not to use it, mostly because on an open Vox raid you have a hard enough time getting people to follow the basics without adding any fancy stuff that requires everyone to know what they're doing.  I thought about it and then envisioned all of the CotHed people running into the bear pit...<br>
<br>
We took her down so I was happy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
You should probably be careful using any tactics like this, I have to imagine VI would consider any assistance from 53+ in the actual battle an exploit.<br>
<br>
Aalek<br>
